The paper discusses the role of physical embodiment in socially interactive robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). It also explores the effect of embodiment on social interactions, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of socially assistive robotics suggests a potential application in systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the review and analysis of existing work involves machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
